# This is the .gitignore file for this repo. It is used to specify files and
# folders that you do not want to be tracked in Git.

# In the context of a replication package, examples of such file include:
#
# - Data files generated by your code.
# - Results generated by your code.
# - Temporary files generated by your code.
# - Raw data that you do not wish to include in the repo due to size, copyright,
#   or confidentiality.
# - Local configuration files that are specific to your computer.

# For example, R will store a history of all R commands you have executed in a
# hidden file called .Rhistory, and will sometimes store the state of the most
# recent R session in a file called .RData. These lines tell Git to ignore any
# file in any folder with these names  
.Rhistory
.RData

# You can tell Git to ignore specific files in specific locations
data/raw_data/auto_raw.csv

# You can use the "*" and "?" characters as wild cards.
# This line tells Git to ignore all Stata data files (.dta) in the
# data/data_for_analysis folder:
data/data_for_analysis/*.dta
# These lines tell Git to ignore all text and PNG files in the 
# results folder
results/*.txt
results/*.png

# Finally, you can tell Git to ignore files in specific folders. These lines tell
# Git to ignore all PNG files in the results/figures folder:
results/figures/

# See <DDD> for additional options
